ne access with authorization2star  aThe country's wars in Iraq and Afghanistan, its interventions around the world, and its global military presence make war, the military, and militarism defining features of contemporary American life. The armed services and the wars they fight shape all aspects of life-from the formation of racial and gendered identities to debates over environmental and immigration policy. Warfare and the military are ubiquitous in popular culture.  At War offers short, accessible essays addressing the central issues in the new military history-ranging from diplomacy and the history of imperialism to the environmental issues that war raises and the ways that war shapes and is shaped by discourses of identity, to questions of who serves in the U.S. military and why and how U.S. wars have been represented in the media and in popular culture.      aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aafghanistan war. 4aafghanistan. 4aarmed services. 4aglobal military. 4aimperialism. 4airaq war. 4airaq. 4amilitarism. 4amilitary culture. 4awar culture. 4awar environment. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAune, Stefan.1 aCarruthers, Susan L.1 aConway-Lanz, Sahr.1 aEllison, Katherine.1 aHamner, Christopher.1 aKieran, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt.1 aKieran, David.1 aKinder, John M.1 aKnauer, Christine.1 aLaderman, Scott.1 aLipman, Jana K.1 aMartini, Edwin A.1 aMartini, Edwin A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt.1 aMiller, Bonnie M.1 aMittelstadt, Jennifer.1 aPiehler, G. Kurt.1 aScott, Wilbur J.1 aTucker, Richard P.1 aVuic, Kara Dixon.1 aWatson, William.1 aWilson, Mark R.1 aWitham, Nick.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of e